Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+):

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class MyTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public MyTests()
    {
        // 4. Create temp files in constructor — Dispose handles cleanup
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    // 1. Windows-only: skipped on other OSes
    [TestMethod]
    [OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
    public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
    {
        var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\...", "Key", null);
        Assert.IsNotNull(value);
    }

    // 2. Skip in CI: runs only locally
    [TestMethod]
    [CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
    public void GpuRendering_ProducesExpectedOutput()
    {
        var result = GpuRenderer.Render();
        Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    }

    // 3. Flaky external API: retry up to 3 times
    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(3)]
    public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
    {
        var forecast = await WeatherClient.GetForecastAsync();
        Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
    }

    // 4. Cleanup runs even if test fails
    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
        {
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Scenario | API | MSTest version |
|---|---|---|
| OS-specific | `[OSCondition(...)]` | 3.10+ |
| Skip in CI | `[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]` | 3.10+ |
| Flaky retries | `[Retry(N)]` | 3.9+ |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `IDisposable` / `[TestCleanup]` | any |

For cleanup, `IDisposable.Dispose()` (or `IAsyncDisposable`) is called after every test, even on failure. Use `[TestCleanup]` if you prefer a method-based approach — both guarantee execution.

> **Note:** Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies, not to mask race conditions or shared-state bugs.
